---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Payload Control Environment";
---

<Layout title={`${title} | Payload Yaw Control`} lang="en">
  <article class="detail-page">
    <h1>{title}</h1>
    <p>
      A simulation environment was developed to control the payload yaw angle.
      The environment includes a crane, controller, payload, suspension ropes,
      and wind disturbances.
    </p>      

    <nav class="page-nav" aria-label="Page navigation">
      <a href="#objective">Control Objective</a>
      <a href="#crane">Crane Rotation</a>
      <a href="#payloads">Payloads</a>
      <a href="#controller">Controller</a>
      <a href="#frequency">Control Frequency</a>
      <a href="#disturbance">Disturbance Conditions</a>
    </nav>

    <section id="objective" class="content-section">
      <h2>Control Objective</h2>

      <p>
        The objective is to rotate the payload to the target yaw angle of
        90° within a control period of approximately 60 seconds.
      </p>

      <div class="objective-grid">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/environment/no-control_en.png`}
            alt="Simulation without payload yaw control"
          />
        </figure>

        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/environment/with-control_en.png`}
            alt="Simulation with payload yaw control"
          />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="crane" class="content-section">
      <h2>Crane Rotation</h2>
      <p>
        The crane rotates by 90° over approximately 55 seconds and then remains
        stationary until the end of the 60-second simulation. During crane
        rotation, the controller continuously regulates the payload toward the
        target yaw angle.
      </p>

      <figure class="wide-figure">
        <img
          src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/environment/crane_rotation.png`}
          alt="Crane rotating to 90 degrees"
        />
        <figcaption>
          Initial, intermediate, and final stages of crane rotation
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section id="payloads" class="content-section">
      <h2>Payloads</h2>
      <p>
        Payloads with two-point and four-point suspension configurations are used
        to evaluate whether the same control method can be applied to payloads
        with different shapes and inertial properties.
      </p>
      <div class="objective-grid">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/environment/HSteel_Plate.png`}
            alt="Relative positions of the crane, controller, and payload"
          />
        <figcaption>
          Relative positions of the crane, controller, and payload
        </figcaption>          
        </figure>

        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/environment/truss.png`}
            alt="Truss payload"
          />
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="controller" class="content-section">
      <h2>Controller</h2>

      <p>
        A controller equipped with four thrusters is mounted above the payload.
        By combining the thrust generated by each thruster, the controller produces
        clockwise or counterclockwise yaw moments to regulate the payload orientation.
      </p>

      <div class="objective-grid">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/environment/thruster.png`}
            alt="Dimensions and weight of the controller"
          />
        </figure>
        <figcaption>
        </figcaption>            
      </div>

      <div class="objective-grid">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/environment/thruster_forces_en.png`}
            alt="Thruster layout and thrust directions"
          />
        </figure>
      </div>
      <dl class="spec-list">
        <div>
          <dt>Thrusters</dt>
          <dd>4</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Maximum Thrust</dt>
          <dd>250 N per thruster</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Output Range</dt>
          <dd>Normalized value (0.0–1.0)</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>

      <p></p>
      <h3>Thruster Output and Payload Yaw</h3>
      <p>
        The following demonstration activates one thruster at a time at its maximum
        output (250 N). Diagonally opposite thrusters generate yaw moments in the
        same rotational direction. During control, the reinforcement learning model
        combines the outputs of all four thrusters to rotate the payload toward the
        target yaw angle.      
      </p>

      <p class="note">
        The Japanese labels in the video indicate the resulting yaw direction:
        clockwise or counterclockwise. The values in brackets represent the
        normalized output vector of the four thrusters.
      </p>      

      <div class="hero-video">
        <video controls muted playsinline preload="metadata">
          <source
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/videos/Thruster_Force0001-1900.mp4`}
            type="video/mp4"
          />
          Your browser does not support HTML5 video.
        </video>
      </div>	  
    </section>

    <section id="frequency" class="content-section">
      <h2>Control Frequency</h2>

      <p>
        The control model updates the outputs of the four thrusters at 3 Hz
        (approximately every 333 ms). Since the simulation runs at 30 fps,
        each computed output is held for approximately 10 frames before the
        next control update.
      </p>

      <div class="control-frequency" aria-label="Relationship between simulation and control frequencies">
        <div>
          <strong>30 fps</strong>
          <span>Simulation</span>
        </div>
        <span class="control-frequency__arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        <div>
          <strong>3 Hz</strong>
          <span>Control Update</span>
        </div>
        <span class="control-frequency__arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        <div>
          <strong>10 frames</strong>
          <span>Output Hold</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="note">
        The actual thrust is calculated by multiplying the normalized output
        (0.0–1.0) by the maximum thrust of each thruster.      
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="disturbance" class="content-section">
      <h2>Disturbance Conditions</h2>

      <p>
        Three disturbance conditions are used to evaluate the control performance:
        no wind, a constant wind in the X direction, and a circular wind disturbance
        whose direction changes over time. The disturbance conditions become
        progressively more challenging, allowing the robustness of the controller
        to be evaluated.
      </p>

      <div class="disturbance-grid">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/environment/X0Y0_en.png`}
            alt="X0Y0 condition with no wind"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">X0Y0</span>
            No Wind
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/environment/X1Y0_en.png`}
            alt="X1Y0 condition with wind in the X direction"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">X1Y0</span>
            X-axis Wind
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/environment/X1Y1_en.png`}
            alt="X1Y1 condition with circular wind disturbance"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">X1Y1</span>
            Circular Wind
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <nav class="detail-navigation" aria-label="Detail page navigation">
      <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/en/overview/`}>
        ← Overview
      </a>
      <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/en/control_model/`}>
          Control Model →
      </a>

    </nav>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .detail-page {
    padding: 32px 0 64px;
  }

  .page-header {
    max-width: 1100px;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .page-header p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  .page-nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 10px 24px;
    margin: 32px 0 56px;
    padding: 16px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
  }

  .page-nav a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .page-nav a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .content-section {
    scroll-margin-top: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 72px;
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }


  .content-section > p {
    margin: 0 0 28px;
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  figcaption {
    margin-top: 0px;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .figure-title {
    display: block;
    color: #222;
  }


  .wide-figure {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 24px auto 0;
  }
  .image-grid,
  .payload-grid,
  .disturbance-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .image-grid--two {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .payload-grid,
  .disturbance-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .spec-list {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    margin: 28px 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
  }

  .spec-list div {
    padding: 18px 20px;
  }

  .spec-list div + div {
    border-left: 1px solid #ddd;
  }

  .spec-list dt {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #666;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .spec-list dd {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .control-frequency {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 20px;
    max-width: 850px;
    margin: 32px 0;
  }

  .control-frequency div {
    padding: 24px 16px;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-radius: 10px;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .control-frequency strong,
  .control-frequency span {
    display: block;
  }

  .control-frequency strong {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .control-frequency__arrow {
    color: #777;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
  }

  .note {
    color: #666;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .detail-navigation {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 24px;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
  }

  .detail-navigation a {
    color: inherit;
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .detail-page {
      padding-top: 24px;
    }

    .page-nav {
      margin-bottom: 44px;
    }

    .content-section {
      margin-bottom: 56px;
    }

    .image-grid--two,
    .payload-grid,
    .disturbance-grid,
    .spec-list {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .spec-list div + div {
      border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
      border-left: 0;
    }

    .control-frequency {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 12px;
    }

    .control-frequency__arrow {
      transform: rotate(90deg);
    }

    .detail-navigation {
      flex-direction: column;
    }
  }

  .objective-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 8px;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .objective-grid figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .objective-grid img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .objective-grid figcaption {
    margin-top: 12px;
  }

  .hero-video {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 24px auto;
  }

  .hero-video video {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }



</style>